  <name>Oracle VirtualBox</name>
  <summary>Virtualize operating systems</summary>
  <description>
    <p>
      VirtualBox is a general-purpose full virtualization software for x86_64 hardware (with version 7.1 additionally for macOS/Arm and with version 7.2 also for Windows/Arm), targeted at laptop, desktop, server and embedded use.
    </p>
    <p>
      This is an unofficial redistribution of the VirtualBox project, with Cyberus Technology's VirtualBox KVM patches, not including the Extension Packs.
      Note: VirtualBox is a trademark owned by Oracle. This project has no affiliation with Oracle.
    </p>
  </description>

